						<summary>

						<p>This records some provision made by an oil-merchant by name <hi rend="bold">Subrahmaṇyaṉ of Kīḷmāndūr</hi> residing at Tiruvīśalūr, for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple with on <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee every day. The temple management and the <hi rend="italic">perunguṟiperumakkaḷ</hi> of the village undertook this maintenance.</p>						

						</summary>
